@Reasoning
Emit Runa-canonical Type declarations from an IDL document. Each message
becomes a "Type called <Name>" block; each enum becomes a "Type <Name>
is ..." union; services are emitted as a block of stub Process
declarations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the document. For each message generate "Type called <Name>:" then
"    <field> as <runa-type>" lines, ending with "End Type". For enums
emit "Type <Name> is: | A | B ... End Type".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "idl_to_runa_types" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ms be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 8
    If ms is not equal to 0:
        Let mc be proc list_length from List with ms
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than mc:
            Let m be proc list_get from List with ms, i
            If m is not equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Type called \""
                Let nm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 0
                If nm is not equal to 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, nm
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\":\n"
                Let fs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 8
                If fs is not equal to 0:
                    Let fc be proc list_length from List with fs
                    Let j be 0
                    While j is less than fc:
                        Let f be proc list_get from List with fs, j
                        If f is not equal to 0:
                            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "    "
                            Let fn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
                            If fn is not equal to 0:
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, fn
                            End If
                            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, " as "
                            Let tn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 8
                            Let mapped be proc map_idl_type_to_runa with tn
                            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, mapped
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                        End If
                        Set j to j plus 1
                    End While
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "End Type\n\n"
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Let es be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 16
    If es is not equal to 0:
        Let ec be proc list_length from List with es
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than ec:
            Let e be proc list_get from List with es, k
            If e is not equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Type "
                Let en_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 0
                If en_name is not equal to 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, en_name
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, " is:\n"
                Let vs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 8
                If vs is not equal to 0:
                    Let vc be proc list_length from List with vs
                    Let v_i be 0
                    While v_i is less than vc:
                        Let ev be proc list_get from List with vs, v_i
                        If ev is not equal to 0:
                            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "    | "
                            Let evn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 0
                            If evn is not equal to 0:
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, evn
                            End If
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                        End If
                        Set v_i to v_i plus 1
                    End While
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "End Type\n\n"
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Map a wire-IDL type name (e.g. "int32") to a Runa type name (e.g.
"Integer"). Unknown types are passed through unchanged.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Linear comparison against the canonical type table.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k) over known types (constant).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns the input string unchanged for unknown types.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "map_idl_type_to_runa" takes wire as Integer returns Integer:
    If wire is equal to 0:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m1 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "int32"
    If m1 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m2 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "int64"
    If m2 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m3 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "uint32"
    If m3 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m4 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "uint64"
    If m4 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m5 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "sint32"
    If m5 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m6 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "sint64"
    If m6 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m7 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "fixed32"
    If m7 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m8 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "fixed64"
    If m8 is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    Let m9 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "float"
    If m9 is equal to 1:
        Return "Float"
    End If
    Let m10 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "double"
    If m10 is equal to 1:
        Return "Float"
    End If
    Let m11 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "bool"
    If m11 is equal to 1:
        Return "Boolean"
    End If
    Let m12 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "string"
    If m12 is equal to 1:
        Return "String"
    End If
    Let m13 be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "bytes"
    If m13 is equal to 1:
        Return "Bytes"
    End If
    Return wire
End Process

@Reasoning
Translate an IdlMessage into a generic SchemaNode (SCHEMA_OBJECT). Each
field becomes an ObjectField with the appropriately-typed schema.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Build a SCHEMA_OBJECT. For each field, decide if its type is one of the
recognized scalars; build a leaf schema; build ObjectField (required if
LABEL_REQUIRED, optional otherwise) and attach.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over fields.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "idl_to_schema" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let union_node be proc schema_create_union from Schema
    If union_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ms be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 8
    If ms is not equal to 0:
        Let mc be proc list_length from List with ms
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than mc:
            Let m be proc list_get from List with ms, i
            If m is not equal to 0:
                Let obj be proc schema_create_object from Schema
                Let fs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 8
                If fs is not equal to 0:
                    Let fc be proc list_length from List with fs
                    Let j be 0
                    While j is less than fc:
                        Let f be proc list_get from List with fs, j
                        If f is not equal to 0:
                            Let fn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
                            Let tn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 8
                            Let lbl be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
                            Let sub be proc leaf_schema_for_idl_type with tn
                            If sub is not equal to 0:
                                Let req_flag be 0
                                If lbl is equal to LABEL_REQUIRED:
                                    Set req_flag to 1
                                End If
                                Let fld be proc object_field_create from Schema with fn, sub, req_flag
                                If fld is not equal to 0:
                                    proc schema_object_add_field from Schema with obj, fld
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set j to j plus 1
                    End While
                End If
                proc schema_union_add_variant from Schema with union_node, obj
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return union_node
End Process

@Reasoning
Build a leaf SchemaNode for a wire-IDL type name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up the type; map "int*" to integer schema, "bool" to boolean,
"string" to string, "bytes" to string (text representation), unknowns to
a reference node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "leaf_schema_for_idl_type" takes wire as Integer returns Integer:
    If wire is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let int_names be proc starts_with_any_int_name with wire
    If int_names is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_integer_any from Schema
    End If
    Let m_bool be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "bool"
    If m_bool is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_boolean from Schema
    End If
    Let m_string be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "string"
    If m_string is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_string_any from Schema
    End If
    Let m_bytes be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "bytes"
    If m_bytes is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_string_any from Schema
    End If
    Let m_float be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "float"
    If m_float is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_float_any from Schema
    End If
    Let m_double be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, "double"
    If m_double is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_float_any from Schema
    End If
    Return proc schema_create_reference from Schema with wire
End Process

@Reasoning
Return 1 if the wire-IDL type name is one of the integer aliases.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Check each int variant by name.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "starts_with_any_int_name" takes wire as Integer returns Integer:
    Let names_int_count be 8
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than names_int_count:
        Let candidate be 0
        If i is equal to 0:
            Set candidate to "int32"
        End If
        If i is equal to 1:
            Set candidate to "int64"
        End If
        If i is equal to 2:
            Set candidate to "uint32"
        End If
        If i is equal to 3:
            Set candidate to "uint64"
        End If
        If i is equal to 4:
            Set candidate to "sint32"
        End If
        If i is equal to 5:
            Set candidate to "sint64"
        End If
        If i is equal to 6:
            Set candidate to "fixed32"
        End If
        If i is equal to 7:
            Set candidate to "fixed64"
        End If
        If candidate is not equal to 0:
            Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with wire, candidate
            If eq is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process
